{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Nuzhat et al. [157] utilized a kNN-based machine learning model to predict the resonant frequencies of Artificial Magnetic Conductor (AMC) cells and compared it with other ML algorithms.",
    "They inputted the structural parameters L and G and simulated 129 sets of resonance curves using ANSYS HFSS as the dataset.",
    "During kNN training, they selected k = 3 as the optimal value.",
    "The results are shown in Figure 5(c), the trained kNN model exhibited good consistency with HFSS and required much less time and computational resources than traditional electromagnetic simulation methods.",
    "Despite its simplicity, kNN demonstrated excellent performance in predicting AMC resonance frequencies due to its ability to handle small-dimensional datasets with a large number of measurement values."
  ]
}